    <h1>Which Fidget Spinner Should I Get?</h1>
    <p>
      If you never had a fidget spinner, this may be a very hard decision to make when choosing which one to buy.
      Not considering there are many clones and ripoffs at unreasonable price that you may fall into.
    </p>
    <p>
      Unlike Fidget Cube which has only one original version. You will be overwhelmed with tons of different fidget spinners in different brand and designs.
    </p>
    <p>
      And to make thing easier for you, I have collected every worthy fidget spinners, grouped by price range.
    </p>
    <div class="clear"></div>
    <h2>1. The Cheapest Fidget Spinners That Doesn't Suck (~$5)</h2>
    <p>
      If you are newbie in the spinner expert field and you have a tight budget. Just go ahead and pick the
      <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Alptoy-Anti-Anxiety-Spinner-Focusing-Adults-Black/dp/B06Y5DXT22" target="_blank">Alptoy spinner for $5.49</a>.
      This spinner is made of plastic with steel bearing. The spinning time is not so bad, at 2 minutes.
      Although its price is low, it doesn't feel like a cheap crap. It also have a very high customer rating on Amazon.
    </p>
    <img src="/img/knowledge/6.png" alt="Cheapest Fidget Spinner" />
    <p>
      If you like metal better, you make take the
      <a href="https://www.amazon.com/ATESSON-Tri-Spinner-Stainless-Precision-Spinning/dp/B06Y5HW7C9/" target="_blank">Atesson spinner for $4.89</a>.
      Although you shouldn't expect a long spin time for price tag like this. It still make up to 1-2 minutes spin.
    </p>
    <img src="/img/knowledge/7.jpg" alt="Cheapest Fidget Spinner" />

    <h2>2. Spinners That You Can Play For Weeks ($10~$20)</h2>
    <p>
      Well although cheap spinner can be a good try at first, they usually don't last for long. Especially after throwing and dropping in few days.
      If you have more than $10 to spend, choose
      <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Zekpro-Anti-Anxiety-Focusing-Adults-Best-Relieves/dp/B01N7T7FPY/" target="_blank">Zekpro spinner ($14.99)</a>.
      It is made of plastic, but not all plastic are the same. This one does looks better,
      feel softer, spin better and more durable to carry everyday.
    </p>
    <img src="/img/knowledge/8.png" alt="Zekpro spinner" />

    <h2>3. Ok. It's Time To Get A Serious Spinner ($30+)</h2>
    <p>
      If you are tired with spinners that are noisy, last 2-3 minutes spin and easily get dirty, then you need to get more serious.
      High quality bearings and design from spinners like <a href="https://aerospinner.com" target="_blank">AeroSpinner ($37.99)</a> will give you 6-8 minutes spin.
      It will also produce less noise, feel great in your hand and look really nice once you get it.
    </p>
    <img src="/img/knowledge/9.png" alt="AeroSpinner" />
    <p>
      The <a href="https://www.etsy.com/listing/531020599/rotobow-nano-ti-hand-spinner" target="_blank">Rotobow Nano Ti ($49.99)</a> is also a good choice when
      you prefer a tiny size spinner made out of Titanium that you can easily put into your pocket.
    </p>
    <img src="/img/knowledge/10.jpg" alt="Rotobow Nano Ti" />
    <h2>4. Premium Spinners ($100+)</h2>
    <p>
      Who says you don't have the money? Try out <a href="https://squareup.com/store/ultraspinners/">Modulator Spinner</a> and have fun with these big boy.
    </p>
    <p>
      Modulator, true to its name, is designed as a spinner that can be modified to fit your spinning pleasure. At it's core, we have a a small 1 inch diameter
      spherical spinner (available in aluminum or brass) with a stainless steel R188 bearing set deep into the middle and concave buttons almost perfectly
      flush on opposite sides of the sphere. One arm, two arms, four arms. Aluminum arms, stainless steel arms, brass arms. This is open design at its finest.
    </p>
